<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="653" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="53.[1361,2566,2820,3199]" pageId="53" pageNumber="653">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1361,1516,2820,2845]" pageId="53" pageNumber="653">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[1541,1683,2820,2845]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hapalomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="53" pageNumber="653" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hapalomys</taxonomicName>
suntsovi Abramov, Balakirev &amp; Rozhnov, 2017, 
<materialsCitation pageId="53" pageNumber="653">“Vietnam, c.13 km NE of Bu Gia Map Village, Bu Gia Map National Park, Binh Phuoc Province, 12°12°N, 107°12’E, elevation 540 m above sea level.”</materialsCitation>
This species was previously included under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1927" box="[1980,2139,2929,2963]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hapalomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="53" pageNumber="653" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delacouri">H. delacouri</taxonomicName>
, which is need of further revision throughout its distribution, and may have a more widespread distribution then what is currently known. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="653" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="653" targetBox="[1154,1158,1206,1231]" targetPageId="54">
<paragraph blockId="53.[1361,2566,2820,3199]" pageId="53" pageNumber="653">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1362,1537,3051,3080]" pageId="53" pageNumber="653">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from Bu Gia Map National Park, Binh Phuoc Province, S Vietnam; perhaps adjacent E Cambodia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
